info.narration:
[
{$0 is perhaps the most active and cheerful girl out of all our Abnormalities. However, there may be more than meets the eye to her.},
{$0 seems to be friendly and good to us for now, but caution should still be maintained.},
{The potential threat $0 possesses is well known to most of our employees. Please remain cautious.},
{In fact, “peace” is not what $0 desires.}
]

[
{$0 is humming while looking out the window, she seems well.},
{$0 welcomes #0 with a radiant smile just as they step through the door.},
{$0 happily greets #0. “What a beautiful day it is!”},
{$0 is evidently glad to see #0.}
]

[
{$0 proudly recounts the time she defeated 3 villains all by herself to #0.},
{#0 listens to one of $0’s stories. Even though she has told this one several times already, she never gets sick of telling it again.},
{$0 is talking about a villain who virtuously reformed because of her. As #0 compliments her for the act, she laughs delightfully.}
]

[
{Her “Magic Shoes” occasionally click together, making a cheerful sound.},
{The “Magic Jewelry” around her neck shimmers in the light.},
{The lace of her luxuriant magical outfit is swinging exuberantly.}
]

[
{$0 speaks of her “Duty” to #0. She whispers that it is very important and secretive.},
{$0 talks about “Justice” to #0. She whispers that her work in itself is justice.}
]

[
{$0 is mumbling inaudibly with a melancholic tone to #0, who has just stepped through the door.},
{Unlike how she usually is, $0 is not paying any attention to #0 who just entered the room.}
]

[
{#0 approaches $0 to see how she’s doing. “Peace is getting tired.”},
{$0 mumbles audibly: “The weather looks good today. Though, I’m not really that happy about it.”}
]

[
{Her “Magic Shoes” tap quietly, breaking the heavy silence.},
{Her eyes are unfocused, and she’s forcing an unusually dreary smile.}
]

[
{$0, a magical girl no longer, gazes at #0 with murderous intent.}
]

[
{$0 figured out that #0 was going to administer anesthetic, and chose to make the first strike.}
]

[
{One of $0’s sharp fangs misses and penetrates #0’s shoulder.}
]

[
{$0 steps over #0’s limp body and exits the room. She will now search for other victims in every corner of the facility.},
{Before breathing their final breath, #0 earnestly tries to speak with $0 using all their might. However, she shuts the door as if she didn’t hear a thing.}
]

observe.desc:
[
{A humanoid Abnormality that looks like it would go and fight villains for peace and justice at any moment.}
]

[
{It is friendly toward every employee and is able to engage in casual conversation. It believes that it is a hero born to save the world, and takes considerable pride in it.}
]

[
{When it shows signs of anxiety or doubt while conversing with an employee, its appearance and personality will undergo an adverse change within 4 days, and it will display symptoms of dissociative disorders. }
]

[
{The definition of “good” and “evil” are fixed in its mind. Some assume that when the Abnormality’s beliefs lead to a horrible doubt about the existence of evil, it will choose to become evil to negate that doubt.}
]

[
{All parameters will return to normal after the negative phase passes, and the Abnormality will have no memory of the behavior it exhibited during that phase. }
]

      [
      {<Audio Log_1>

      Employee: How are you feeling today?
      Magical Girl: Good. The world is at peace, and it’s quiet around here. Peace is a great thing to have. It means there aren't any villains around, right?}
      ]

      [
      {<Audio Log_4>

      (The Abnormality endlessly mumbles to itself, without even noticing the employee in its containment)
      Magical Girl: The world can be divided into good and evil. I am on the side of justice. If I am on the side of good, then someone has to be on the side of evil. Without someone to play the villain, I can't exist. Then, who is going to protect the world?

<Audio Cuts Out>}
      ]
